Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.94,0:01:36.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If cases were all men,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.61,0:01:38.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then I wonder if the unseen puzzles would be women?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.03,0:01:40.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Beetles, stag beetles, and even a Buddha statue?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.45,0:01:42.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The Detective Boys' big search!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.12,0:01:43.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.70,0:01:45.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.54,0:01:48.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.35,0:00:06.11,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.11,0:00:07.98,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, let me touch it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.40,0:00:10.36,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all prickly. It looks painful.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.90,0:00:12.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My dad bought it for me at the department store.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.95,0:00:14.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got a stag beetle at my house too!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.12,0:00:21.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no point in having it unless you catch it yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.12,0:00:24.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But you {\i1}do{\i0} want a beetle, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.30,0:00:24.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.98,0:00:28.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A beetle?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.65,0:00:32.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's what you want. You really are kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.96,0:00:35.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can catch as many beetles as you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.10,0:00:38.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.67,0:00:41.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't forgive you if it's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.10,0:00:44.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I have an old friend in Yamanashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.47,0:00:49.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He says I can come and see him anytime I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.24,0:00:52.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You should be able to catch as many beetles as you want there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.53,0:00:57.66,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And so, we ended up visiting the doc's old friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.91,0:01:01.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all the way in the middle of the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.99,0:01:05.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like we're going to catch a lot of beetles and stag beetles here!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.44,0:01:07.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Absolutely!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.65,0:01:11.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There might even be a Hercules beetle too!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.55,0:01:15.30,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There's no way there'd be such a thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,[SIGN: Tsuchi'inishieka Station]{This is the literal reading and needs to be changed -dylanborja}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.10,0:03:28.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he'd meet us here, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.79,0:03:31.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There isn't a single convenience store.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.27,0:03:32.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And no vending machines, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.05,0:03:34.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Agasa.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.10,0:03:38.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryūtarō, long time no see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.52,0:03:40.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you been well?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.57,0:03:43.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.09,0:03:44.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me introduce you to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.03,0:03:50.66,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryūtarō Namatame (52)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.36,0:03:46.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my friend, Ryūtarō Namatame.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,[SIGN: Namatame Ryūtarō (52)]
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.32,0:03:49.62,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice of you to come, kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.62,0:03:50.66,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.20,0:03:52.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.64,0:03:56.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You said your house was at the foot of the mountain, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.93,0:03:58.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it far from here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.66,0:04:02.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's only about an hour by car.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.21,0:04:05.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, I'm so thirsty I could die.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.32,0:04:06.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there anything I can drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.95,0:04:09.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What a helpless kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.55,0:04:11.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,[SIGN: Roadside Station]{I translated "michi no eki" as "Roadside Station." It can be changed. -dylanborja}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.17,0:04:21.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have a cola, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.67,0:04:24.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A big helping of soft ice cream for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.07,0:04:25.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What shall I have?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.29,0:04:29.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kei!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.58,0:04:35.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're eating lunch here, that means you've been playing pachinko again, haven't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.76,0:04:37.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, I haven't!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.41,0:04:39.83,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, how rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.87,0:04:43.38,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Kei Yabe (27)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,[SIGN: Yabe Kei (27)]
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.83,0:04:43.38,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,I just brought some watermelon I grew to this market!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.26,0:04:45.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.90,0:04:49.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you get into debt and make your mother cry again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.93,0:04:51.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.98,0:04:54.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a beetle. It's big!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.97,0:04:58.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a Miyama Stag Beetle, too. It's so cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.22,0:04:59.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.10,0:05:02.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Those aren't toys! Don't touch them!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,[SIGN: Ikeda Shūhei (50)]
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.32,0:05:08.95,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Shūhei Ikeda (50)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.61,0:05:06.86,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone from a department store\Nin Tōkyō's coming to buy them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.86,0:05:08.99,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,If they're weakened then they can't be sold!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.35,0:05:12.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shūhei, the children were just looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.95,0:05:14.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's all the fuss about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.82,0:05:17.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryūtarō, you know these folks?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.25,0:05:20.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. They're guests from Tōkyō.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.46,0:05:25.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't come onto my mountain just because you want beetles.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.72,0:05:29.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What a greeting after we just got here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.17,0:05:32.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, how pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.84,0:05:34.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.54,0:05:38.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since he was a child, Shūhei's been stingy and skeptical.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.53,0:05:42.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, we've had disputes over the borders of our land.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.23,0:05:47.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,'Disputes over land...' Are you rich?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.11,0:05:49.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be silly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.76,0:05:52.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, since I live on a farm I don't have trouble getting something to eat, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.57,0:05:54.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.12,0:05:57.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But you're able to house all of us, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.58,0:06:01.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an old house, but it has a lot of\Nrooms, so don't worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.83,0:06:04.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there's a lot of old junk too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.54,0:06:07.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone from an antique shop who came by the other day
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.31,0:06:09.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,said that the Buddha statue that had fallen near the alcove
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.67,0:06:12.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,might be from the Kamakura Period.{I translated "toko no ma" as "alcove." It can be changed. -dylanborja}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.97,0:06:14.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll go with this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.04,0:06:17.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.36,0:06:28.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This painting... it's kind of scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.01,0:06:31.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is why children are helpless.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.95,0:06:34.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It might be by Maruyama Ōkyo. {historical character, doesn't get nameflipped}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.01,0:06:37.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That Buddha statue may have been made by Unkei.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.62,0:06:41.16,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Yeah, right...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.13,0:06:45.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who cares about that? Let's hurry up and go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.73,0:06:47.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.17,0:06:51.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We're totally going to catch a stag beetle and brag to everyone in class!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.55,0:06:52.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.38,0:06:59.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Should we start around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.35,0:07:02.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They're here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.23,0:07:07.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know, but beetles and stag beetles like these kinds of oak and Japanese oak trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.60,0:07:09.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It reeks of liquor!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.82,0:07:12.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd you put a good banana in liquor?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.33,0:07:15.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind that. Open the stocking.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.83,0:07:16.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.35,0:07:23.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was wondering why you told all of us to bring an old stocking, but it was for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.30,0:07:28.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My dad asked my if I was going to play robbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.40,0:07:30.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we really going to be able to catch one by doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.59,0:07:33.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to have to wait until tonight to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.61,0:07:34.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This ought to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.90,0:07:36.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's put some more up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.43,0:07:40.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope it gets dark quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.98,0:07:46.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are these tools for?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.31,0:07:50.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What would someone be doing at a place like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.11,0:07:52.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The key's still here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.61,0:07:54.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! What're you looking at?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.99,0:07:58.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, no, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.38,0:08:00.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The pachinko guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.80,0:08:03.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I said that I don't do such a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.32,0:08:06.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you guys doing at a place like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.02,0:08:07.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We thought we'd catch some beetles.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.74,0:08:10.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't come near my car!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.85,0:08:12.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now go!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.59,0:08:14.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We were just taking a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.88,0:08:16.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just go already!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.52,0:08:18.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't go, you'll be sorry!!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.38,0:08:19.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.16,0:08:19.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.27,0:08:24.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't have to get that angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.60,0:08:28.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think there might be something in there that he doesn't want others to see?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.03,0:08:29.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.65,0:08:37.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As usual, you're still making weird inventions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.99,0:08:39.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,'Weird' is uncalled for.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.53,0:08:45.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's about time already.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.25,0:08:47.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.54,0:08:51.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you'll be all right, but there are snakes around here, so take care of yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.20,0:08:55.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd be worried if the children went by themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.19,0:08:57.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to go with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.36,0:08:59.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryūtarō, go ahead and go to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.56,0:09:05.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Beetles! There's some beetles!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.70,0:09:08.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing! Let me touch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.85,0:09:10.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.06,0:09:14.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Let's catch a bunch more!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.72,0:09:16.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a Giant Stag Beetle!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.94,0:09:19.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look! It's a Nokogiri Stag Beetle!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.81,0:09:23.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing! This is the first time I've seen so many!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.96,0:09:25.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How about this one?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.47,0:09:28.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mine's bigger!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.41,0:09:30.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's make them fight right after we get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.79,0:09:33.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.88,0:09:39.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez. You can never let your guard down around that damn Ryūtarō.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.80,0:09:43.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Making me sneak around like this...\NI won't let him get away with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.37,0:09:46.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That guy... from earlier today...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.77,0:09:51.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone from a department store\Nin Tōkyō's going to be coming to buy them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.23,0:09:53.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If they're weakened then they can't be sold!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.11,0:09:56.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the man we met at the Roadside Station.{I translated "michi no eki" as "Roadside Station." It can be changed. -dylanborja}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.91,0:09:59.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He said something about Ryūtarō.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.16,0:10:02.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Lots of fish, lots of fish!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.60,0:10:04.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a sailer, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.45,0:10:07.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like that guy is still awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.62,0:10:09.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange. The sliding doors are open.{I translated "shouji" as "sliding doors." It can be changed. -dylanborja}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.18,0:10:17.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mister! Hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.28,0:10:18.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.58,0:10:19.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryūtarō!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.72,0:10:21.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.91,0:10:24.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, I'm calling an ambulance now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.83,0:10:30.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Miyama... Stag Beetle...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.31,0:10:33.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you say 'Miyama Stag Beetle?'
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.46,0:10:34.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.02,0:10:38.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara! An ambulance!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.77,0:10:39.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.63,0:10:42.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.64,0:10:44.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.85,0:10:46.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The Buddha statue that was here is gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.46,0:10:50.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, hurry up and call!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.02,0:10:50.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.79,0:10:52.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Out of service!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.92,0:10:59.59,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.22,0:11:06.47,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Either way, what did he mean by 'Miyama Stag Beetle...'
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.26,0:11:15.85,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Namatame{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was transported to the hospital while unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.48,0:11:19.15,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And then, the police investigation began.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,[SIGN: Detective Motohashi (45)]
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.44,0:11:23.48,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Motohashi (45)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.52,0:11:22.02,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,'Miyama Stag Beetle?'
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.02,0:11:23.48,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Did he really say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.48,0:11:24.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.78,0:11:27.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We heard it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.04,0:11:27.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.11,0:11:31.87,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Fuji'i (27)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.65,0:11:31.87,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not something you'd think someone would say before losing consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.54,0:11:34.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think it means?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.21,0:11:35.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.31,0:11:38.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... There's one more thing that's bothering me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.78,0:11:39.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.71,0:11:44.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The Buddha statue that was over there when we left is missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.51,0:11:46.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Buddha statue?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.96,0:11:52.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it, a Buddha statue robbery case has been going on at temples throughout the prefecture lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.05,0:11:58.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When the victim caught them trying to steal the Buddha statue, the thief struck him with a nearby pot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.97,0:12:00.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's settled.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.05,0:12:00.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.83,0:12:01.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.73,0:12:05.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This was on his clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.89,0:12:07.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's some kind of hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.63,0:12:09.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just in case, run it through forensics.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.37,0:12:10.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.49,0:12:15.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, why did Ryūtarō say 'Miyama Stag Beetle?'
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.45,0:12:18.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way a Miyama Stag Beetle could've done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.62,0:12:21.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, when we were coming back, we saw that man, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.21,0:12:26.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can never let your guard down around that damn Ryūtarō.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.21,0:12:31.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That guy had a Miyama Stag Beetle at the Roadside Station!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.76,0:12:33.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.85,0:12:36.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Namatame{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} called him Shūhei.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.43,0:12:41.89,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Officer Iwanaga (55)
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.85,0:12:40.89,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that's Shūhei Ikeda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who lives in this village.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,[SIGN: Officer Iwanaga (55)]
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.35,0:12:45.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,L-Let me go! Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.64,0:12:47.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd I do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.94,0:12:52.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You've been having disputes with Namatame{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} over the borders of your lands, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.92,0:12:56.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. That's been my land for generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.05,0:12:58.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He tried to make a field out of it on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.39,0:13:00.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.91,0:13:03.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where were you at around 12:00 last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.86,0:13:04.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,12:00...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.79,0:13:06.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were walking in the street, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.79,0:13:11.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And very angrily you said 'You can never let your guard down around that damn Ryūtarō.'
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.14,0:13:13.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.84,0:13:15.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.38,0:13:19.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When I went to patrol, the rice field's water had been stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.16,0:13:21.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryūtarō's the only one who would do that,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.88,0:13:25.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I thought I'd give him a good talking-to the next time I see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.40,0:13:28.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you 'give him a good talking-to' last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.44,0:13:31.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No... I would never do such a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.64,0:13:32.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.18,0:13:41.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, did you know there was a Buddha statue put up as an ornament in the alcove in the guest room?{I translated "toko no ma" as "alcove" and "zashiki" as "guest room." It can be changed. -dylanborja}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.71,0:13:43.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Buddha statue? Oh yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.99,0:13:46.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a terribly old and dirty thing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.13,0:13:51.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that the one who attacked Namatame{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} took that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.76,0:13:53.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And it wasn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.41,0:13:54.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Took the Buddha statue?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.78,0:13:57.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. A Buddha statue thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.70,0:14:00.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I have someone in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.43,0:14:01.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.76,0:14:02.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Kei.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.77,0:14:05.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He had a coping saw and a grinder,\Namong other things, piled up in his truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.72,0:14:09.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought he was suspicious for going out night after night.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.76,0:14:11.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Those were definitely piled up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.40,0:14:14.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. He got really angry when we saw them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.53,0:14:16.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really. It was scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.41,0:14:22.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Now that you mention it, that guy was wearing a T-shirt with a picture of a Miyama Stag Beetle!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.40,0:14:28.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.44,0:14:30.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.70,0:14:33.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We have a few things we'd like to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.15,0:14:34.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you come with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.79,0:14:36.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.97,0:14:38.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd I do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.66,0:14:42.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where were you at around 12:00 last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.83,0:14:44.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,12:00...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.35,0:14:46.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it obvious that I was at home?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.70,0:14:47.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.88,0:14:51.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,On my way back from my rice field patrol, I passed by the front of your house,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.29,0:14:52.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but your truck wasn't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.42,0:14:55.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You entered this house to steal the Buddha statue,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.95,0:14:59.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,where you were found by Namatame{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nso you struck his head and fled.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.13,0:14:59.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.50,0:15:02.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.44,0:15:05.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't come here by car to steal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.60,0:15:08.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right? It's a short walk!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.33,0:15:11.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then where were you at around 12:00 last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.27,0:15:12.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.00,0:15:17.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I didn't attack Namatame. I mean it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.75,0:15:20.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find out what that hair is?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.16,0:15:22.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. That was a dog's hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.43,0:15:24.72,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A dog, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.61,0:15:34.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What would someone be doing at a place like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.32,0:15:36.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The car key was left in.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.69,0:15:38.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! What're you looking at?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.34,0:15:53.88,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.76,0:16:00.68,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The one who attacked Namatame{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} isn't either one of those two.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.72,0:16:04.06,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If so, who on Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.19,0:16:13.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you looking at?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.30,0:16:16.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's you, Haibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.28,0:16:19.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't 'it's you, Haibara' me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.70,0:16:21.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you intend to do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.66,0:16:23.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't either of those two.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.91,0:16:28.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But both of them have a connection with Miyama Stag Beetles.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.58,0:16:31.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If it was one of those two, then Namatame{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} should have said their name.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.96,0:16:34.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.32,0:16:36.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.42,0:16:40.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I can tell you at least that the person who attacked Namatame{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.13,0:16:42.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}did{\i0} take that Buddha statue.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.89,0:16:47.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that dirty Buddha statue really that valuable?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.72,0:16:48.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.98,0:16:51.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He said it was made in the Kamakura Period, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.90,0:16:54.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Namatame{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said it may have been made by Unkei.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.52,0:16:59.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there's still Unkei works left over from the Kamakura Period, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.53,0:17:01.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be from the Heian Period?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.65,0:17:04.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I'm sure I heard it was from the Kamakura Period.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.79,0:17:06.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now where did I hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.49,0:17:11.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there's a lot of old junk too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.37,0:17:14.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone from an antique shop who came by the other day
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.17,0:17:16.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,said that the Buddha statue that had fallen near the alcove
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.54,0:17:19.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,might be from the Kamakura Period.{I translated "toko no ma" as "alcove." It can be changed. -dylanborja}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.40,0:17:21.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was at that Roadside Station.{I translated "michi no eki" as "Roadside Station." It can be changed. -dylanborja}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.61,0:17:25.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara, let's go back to that Roadside Station!{I translated "michi no eki" as "Roadside Station." It can be changed. -dylanborja}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.19,0:17:30.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We came here yesterday, but do you remember us?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.24,0:17:33.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I don't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.71,0:17:35.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If there's something that you noticed...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.32,0:17:40.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss, we came here yesterday, but do you remember us?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.24,0:17:43.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Weren't you some of the children with Namatame{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.24,0:17:44.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.20,0:17:48.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there anyone else at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.05,0:17:49.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.25,0:17:52.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, how pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.05,0:17:56.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there was a young married couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.82,0:17:59.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember anything about those people?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.67,0:18:01.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you say that...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.53,0:18:04.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I only remember them buying a potted plant.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.34,0:18:05.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of potted plant was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.74,0:18:07.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.05,0:18:11.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't it have an interesting name?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.68,0:18:14.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Although it's not really to our taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.08,0:18:15.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.15,0:18:19.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What on Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.93,0:18:21.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.53,0:18:27.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, that young married couple... weren't they...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.50,0:18:30.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, how nice of you to know that. That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.96,0:18:37.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} go? {haibara isn't directly mentioned in the dialogue, but haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is how mitsuhiko would refer to her normally}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.58,0:18:39.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Along with the doc.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.54,0:18:43.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't think they're having lunch, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.16,0:18:46.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, let's continue this conversation at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.19,0:18:51.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I said this has nothing to do with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.10,0:18:52.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Me neither!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.31,0:18:53.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.60,0:18:56.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-All of a sudden again...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.02,0:18:59.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Neither one of those two did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.11,0:19:00.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.82,0:19:05.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Although, Kei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} {\i1}is{\i0} guilty of being a Buddha statue thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.34,0:19:06.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't say stupid things!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.95,0:19:10.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw it underneath your car.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.74,0:19:13.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The Buddha statue was tied to the chassis.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.79,0:19:16.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you steal it from some temple last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.58,0:19:23.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you be so sure that neither one of these two attacked Namatame{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.69,0:19:25.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason is simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.66,0:19:28.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryūtarō knows both of their names.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.84,0:19:31.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He wouldn't have said something like 'Miyama Stag Beetle.'
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.95,0:19:33.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Since it was dark or something,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.52,0:19:37.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when he was suddenly attacked, wouldn't he not have been able to see the attacker's face?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.52,0:19:42.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When we got back, the lights in the guest room, the crime scene, were on.{I translated "zashiki" as "guest room." It can be changed. -dylanborja}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.40,0:19:44.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryūtarō went to bed,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.78,0:19:47.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but he heard something, so he came to the guest room
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.36,0:19:49.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and was attacked when he turned on the lights.{I translated "zashiki" as "guest room." It can be changed. -dylanborja}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.45,0:19:53.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What if the attacker's face was hidden?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.62,0:19:58.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even then, Ryūtarō would've probably known which of these two it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.27,0:20:04.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is, we went to a Roadside Station on our way here yesterday.{I translated "michi no eki" as "Roadside Station." It can be changed. -dylanborja}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.84,0:20:11.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There, Ryūtarō bragged that the now-stolen Buddha statue was from the Kamakura Period.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.18,0:20:15.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At the time, a married couple was there that seemed to be tourists.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.84,0:20:20.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That married couple bought a potted plant at the Roadside Station.{I translated "michi no eki" as "Roadside Station." It can be changed. -dylanborja}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.12,0:20:23.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.82,0:20:28.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.53,0:20:30.53,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Miyama\NStag\NBeetle
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.53,0:20:30.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,[SIGN: Miyama Stag Beetle]
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.03,0:20:32.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.57,0:20:35.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,'Miyama Stag Beetle' wasn't an insect.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.95,0:20:38.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was the name of this flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.79,0:20:42.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryūtarō saw the attacker, but he didn't know their name.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.71,0:20:48.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So he wanted to say that the culprit was the person who bought the potted Miyama Stag Beetle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.61,0:20:50.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.72,0:20:52.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there any proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.90,0:20:56.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,According to the person who sold the potted plant,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.56,0:21:00.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that married couple was carrying a Maltese.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.20,0:21:01.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maltese?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.25,0:21:05.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The thing that got onto Ryūtarō's clothes was also the hair of a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.17,0:21:09.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you do a DNA test, it should make it clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.88,0:21:13.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit is without a doubt that married couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.66,0:21:16.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I leave the rest to you, detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.95,0:21:23.96,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Afterwards, the police investigated\Npet-friendly hotels and guest houses
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.96,0:21:26.25,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and discovered the identity of the married couple.{I translated "penshon" or "pension" as "guest house"}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.88,0:21:28.88,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The married couple that was arrested in Tōkyō
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.88,0:21:32.88,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}heard that the Buddha statue was from the Kamakura Period, thought they could sell it for a lot,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.88,0:21:35.55,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}so followed the car that we got into,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.55,0:21:37.76,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and later entered the Namatame residence to steal it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.90,0:21:41.93,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}However, when they took the Buddha statue to an antique shop,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.93,0:21:44.52,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}they were told that it wasn't an Unkei or anything special
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.52,0:21:47.27,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and that its value was ¥5,000 at best.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.02,0:21:52.07,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Namatame{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was safely discharged\Nfrom the hospital a few days later.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.77,0:23:23.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.41,0:23:24.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't they cool, guys?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.74,0:23:26.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We caught them ourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.67,0:23:28.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They're Giant Stag... Beetles.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.50,0:23:32.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This flower's called 'Miyama Stag Beetle?'
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.44,0:23:33.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.97,0:23:35.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really giving it to the class?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.95,0:23:41.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My mum said it's a rare flower so I should show everybody in class too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.84,0:23:43.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's set up a schedule for watering it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.78,0:23:45.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds nice! How do we pick?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.44,0:23:47.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too bad you can't brag about those.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.06,0:23:50.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.49,0:24:02.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Cœur, how've you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.01,0:24:03.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.15,0:24:06.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like a map.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.45,0:24:08.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it a treasure map?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.63,0:24:17.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe this map has no connection with a cat burglar but instead, it's about Kōzuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s case.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.88,0:24:24.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan: 'The Great Dog Cœur's Triumph II'
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.89,0:24:29.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint: Cigarette butts!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.81,0:24:31.90,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's Tanabata!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.90,0:24:33.11,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,A {\i1}botamochi{\i0} off the rack!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.11,0:24:34.11,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a godsend.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.90,0:24:33.11,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}tana
